The electrochemical impedance spectroscopy was carried out to analyze the interfacial charge transfer properties of 0.10 and 1.00 wt% Ni-doped and un-doped TiO2 based devices. The electron transport properties at each interfacial were evaluated using Nyquist plots of EIS measurements. All measurements were taken in a two-electrode system using open circuit voltage (VOC) of the DSSC as the biased voltage at the frequency range between 10−2 and 106 Hz under the illumination of 100 mWcm−2.
